properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 3 at 7:30PM MST until January 4 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HAZARDOUS TRAVEL CONDITIONS WILL CONTINUE ALONG INTERSTATE 80
BETWEEN LARAMIE AND RAWLINS THROUGH AT LEAST SATURDAY AFTERNOON...

* WHAT...Wind gusts up to 70 MPH will result in periods of blowing
and drifting snow, as well as sheeting of ice on roadways.

* WHERE...Arlington and Elk Mountain along Interstate 80 between
Laramie and Rawlins.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Expect periods of reduced visibilities and slick
roadways.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST SATURDAY... ...BLIZZARD WARNING IS CANCELLED
